Physiognomical details provided by the chronicler Jan D&lt;U+0142&gt;ugosz. Turnbull, Tannenberg 1410: Disaster for the Teutonic Knights, 23.↩

&quot;Wherever he traveled, he always carried a razor, scissors, brushes, and an ivory comb. He shaved his beard daily, and to the surprise of all the Poles, he even bathed every day.&quot; M.Kuczynski, quoted by Vanda Sruogien&lt;U+0117&gt;-Sruoga, Jogaila (1350&lt;U+2013&gt;1434)↩
And according to mid-fifteenth-century chronicler Jan D&lt;U+0142&gt;ugosz, his pleasures further included the exercise of a prodigious sex drive, &quot;not only in permitted ways but also in forbidden ones&quot;. Quoted by Turnbull, Tannenberg 1410: Disaster for the Teutonic Knights, 23.↩
