Stone, 11.; Plokhy, 98.↩
Sedlar, 282; New Cambridge Medieval History, 711. The Lithuanian inheritance, however, could not be taken for granted. &quot;Jagiello's death in 1434 ended the personal union between the two realms, and it was not clear what would take its place.&quot; Stone, 22.↩
